description: Disconnect the two-cable pair that normally connects the output of control module 1 to control module 2. With all switches ON and the battery installed, use a voltmeter to identify which of the two output cables of control module 1 is at +12 V with respect to the power‑supply 0 V reference, and which is at 0 V. Record the polarity of both cables., outcome='Control Output Cable (+) 1 is at approximately +12 V with respect to the 0 V reference.  \nControl Output Cable (−) 1 is at 0 V with respect to the 0 V reference.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=40.0, cost_breakdown=[('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> Load module input cables,
description: Disconnect the two cables that normally connect control module 8 to the load module. With all switches ON and the battery installed, measure each of the two free cables coming from control module 8 with respect to the power‑supply 0 V reference to determine which is at +12 V and which is at 0 V. Then measure the two input terminals of the load module relative to the same reference to determine which side is internally connected to the series diode (i.e., intended 12 V input) and which is 0 V. Record the polarity of both the upstream cables and the load‑module terminals so that any polarity inversion or mis‑connection at the load can be identified., outcome='All four measured points are at 0.0 V relative to the 0 V reference: Control Output Cable (+) 8, Control Output Cable (−) 8, Load Input Cable (+), and Load Input Cable (−). No polarity difference between the cables or between the load-module inputs can be determined from these readings.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=80.0, cost_breakdown=[('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> Intermediate control-module outputs (modules 2–7),
description: With all switches ON and the battery installed, sequentially disconnect the output pair of each control module i (for i = 2 … 7) from the input of module i+1. For each disconnected pair, measure both cables with respect to the power‑supply 0 V reference to determine whether one is at +12 V and the other at 0 V, or whether both are at 0 V. Record where along the chain the transition occurs from a proper 12 V/0 V pair (as seen at control module 1 output) to a pair that is both at 0 V (as seen at control module 8 output)., outcome='Control Output Cable (+) 2 is at approximately +12 V relative to 0 V, while Control Output Cable (−) 2 is at 0 V. All subsequent control output cables (+/−) for modules 3 through 7 are at 0 V with respect to the power‑supply 0 V reference.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=240.0, cost_breakdown=[('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> Control module 2 internal circuit and indicator LED,
description: Open the inspection panel of control module 2. With all switches ON and the battery installed, and with module 2 still connected in the chain, probe inside the module: (1) measure the voltage between its 12 V input node and 0 V input node, (2) measure the voltage directly across the series resistor–red LED indicator, and (3) visually check whether the red LED is actually present in its holder and whether it lights. Record whether 12 V is present across the module’s input pair and whether the internal indicator circuit has continuity and correct polarity., outcome='12 V is present at Control Module 2’s input: Control Input Cable (+) 2 is at 11.9893 V and Control Input Cable (−) 2 is at 0 V. The power-flow indicator path is non-functional because both ‘Power Flow Indicator Resistor 2’ and ‘Power Flow Indicator (green) 2’ are physically missing and cannot be replaced.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=135.0, cost_breakdown=[('open_inspection_panel', 5.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('test_diode', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None)] 
